│                                                             │
│  ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │ DateTimePicker│    │             App                  │  │
│  │  (CTkFrame)  │    │          (ctk.CTk)                │  │
│  │              │    │                                   │  │
│  │ .date        │    │  Filter frame  │  Table + Logs   │  │
│  │ .hour        │    │  (pool, queue, │  (ttk.Treeview, │  │
│  │ .minute      │    │   date/time)   │   CTkTextbox)   │  │
│  │ .second      │    │                │                 │  │
│  │              │    │  Actions panel (buttons)          │  │
│  └──────────────┘    └──────────────────────────────────┘  │
│                                  │                          │
│              ┌───────────────────┼──────────────────────┐  │
│              ▼                   ▼                       ▼  │
│       Main Thread          Background Threads            │  │
│    (UI events only)    (_search, _reprocess_worker,      │  │
│                         _process_fg, _maybe_advance)     │  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
         │                        │
         ▼                        ▼
   SQL Server DB           Web Service (HTTP POST)
   (pyodbc)                (requests.Session)
```

**Key architectural principle:** The main thread handles only UI events. All database queries and HTTP calls run in daemon background threads. Results are marshalled back to the main thread exclusively via `self.after(0, callback)`.

