## 5. Environment & Configuration

ARM uses `python-dotenv` to load a `.env` file at startup. `load_env()` resolves the path relative to `sys._MEIPASS` (PyInstaller bundle) or the working directory.

### `.env` keys

| Key | Required | Example | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `WEB_SERVICES` | ✅ | `https://host/api/run` | Web service endpoint URL |
| `DB2_DRIVER` | ✅ | `ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server` | ODBC driver name |
| `DB2_SERVER` | ✅ | `sqlserver01` | Database server hostname or IP |
| `DB2_DATABASE` | ✅ | `ProductionDB` | Database name |
| `DB2_TRUSTED` | ✅ | `yes` | Windows integrated auth (`yes`/`no`) |

`WEB_SERVICES` is validated immediately after loading. If absent, the application raises `ValueError` and exits before any window is shown.

### `resource_path(relative_path)`

```python
def resource_path(relative_path):
    base_path = getattr(sys, "_MEIPASS", None) or os.path.abspath(".")
    return os.path.join(base_path, relative_path)
```

Used for all file reads (SQL files). `sys._MEIPASS` is the temp directory PyInstaller extracts bundled files to at runtime, ensuring SQL files are found whether running from source or as a compiled `.exe`.

