### 6.2 Class: `DateTimePicker`

**Inherits:** `ctk.CTkFrame`

A reusable composite widget that combines a `tkcalendar.DateEntry` calendar picker with three `CTkComboBox` dropdowns (hour, minute, second) and a static `(CET)` label.

#### Constructor

```python
DateTimePicker(master, label, default_time=("00", "00", "00"))
```

| Parameter | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `master` | `ctk.CTkFrame` | Parent widget |
| `label` | `str` | Label text displayed to the left (e.g. `"From Date"`) |
| `default_time` | `tuple[str, str, str]` | Default values for hour, minute, second dropdowns |

#### Attributes

| Attribute | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `self.date` | `DateEntry` | Calendar date picker (`yyyy-mm-dd` format) |
| `self.hour` | `CTkComboBox` | Hour selector (values `"00"` – `"23"`) |
| `self.minute` | `CTkComboBox` | Minute selector (values `"00"` – `"59"`) |
| `self.second` | `CTkComboBox` | Second selector (values `"00"` – `"59"`) |

#### Method: `get_cet_datetime() → datetime | None`

Reads the four widget values, parses them into a naive `datetime`, then attaches the `Europe/Berlin` timezone using `pytz.localize(dt, is_dst=False)`.

`is_dst=False` is intentional — during the clock-back DST transition (when clocks go from 03:00 back to 02:00, making times between 02:00–03:00 ambiguous), this always picks the post-DST standard time interpretation instead of raising `pytz.exceptions.AmbiguousTimeError`.

Returns `None` on any parse error (also prints to stdout).

