## 10. State Management

ARM maintains two mutable state objects that cross the main/background thread boundary:

### `self.processed` — `set[str]`

| Operation | Where | When |
|---|---|---|
| `.clear()` | Main thread | On Search start; on auto-advance |
| `.add(serial)` | Background thread | Before each `_process_fg` call |
| `in self.processed` | Background thread | Deduplication check |

**Thread safety:** CPython `set.add` and `in` are GIL-protected. Safe without a lock in CPython.

### `self.result_data` — `dict[str, dict]`

| Operation | Where | When |
|---|---|---|
| `[serial] = {...}` | Background thread | After each API call in `_process_fg` |
| `.get(serial, {})` | Main thread | In `view_data` and `export_excel` |

**Thread safety:** CPython dict assignment and read are GIL-protected. Safe without a lock in CPython.

