## 11. Error Handling Strategy

ARM uses a layered error handling strategy:

| Layer | Mechanism | Behaviour |
|---|---|---|
| Startup | `raise ValueError` | Hard fail — application won't start without `.env` |
| DB connection | `try/except` in every function | Logs error, shows dialog, returns empty result |
| SQL file not found | `try/except` around `open()` | Logs error, function returns early |
| API call exception | `try/except requests.Exception` | Logs as `Request error`, stores `"Error"` status, continues |
| API non-200 | Status code check | Logs as `Failed (HTTP NNN)`, stores `"Failed"` status, continues |
| Background thread unhandled | Outer `try/except` in each worker | Logs error, shows error dialog, releases resources in `finally` |
| UI helper calls from thread | Always via `self.after(0, ...)` | Guaranteed to run on main thread, no race condition |

All `finally` blocks guarantee that DB connections and requests sessions are closed even when exceptions occur mid-processing.

