## 14. Packaging with PyInstaller

ARM supports packaging as a single Windows `.exe` using PyInstaller. The `resource_path()` helper handles the `sys._MEIPASS` extraction directory automatically.

### Recommended spec file options

```bash
pyinstaller arm_app.py \
  --onefile \
  --windowed \
  --name ARM \
  --add-data "sql;sql" \
  --add-data ".env;." \
  --hidden-import customtkinter \
  --hidden-import tkcalendar \
  --hidden-import pyodbc \
  --hidden-import pytz
```

| Flag | Reason |
|---|---|
| `--onefile` | Single `.exe` output |
| `--windowed` | Suppress the console window on Windows |
| `--add-data "sql;sql"` | Bundle the `sql/` directory (Windows separator is `;`) |
| `--add-data ".env;."` | Bundle the `.env` file into the root of the extracted temp dir |
| `--hidden-import` | PyInstaller may not detect these dynamically-used imports |

> **Security note:** Bundling `.env` into the executable embeds credentials. For production, consider shipping the `.env` separately and documenting that it must sit alongside the `.exe`.

